.SH "NAME"
Class::DBI::Lite::ColumnInfo \- Extended meta\-information about database table fields.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&  foreach my $field ( app::artist\->columns )
\&  {
\&  
\&  }# end foreach()
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Sometimes database table field information needs to be available during runtime.
.PP
This class provides a simple interface to query a specific database field.
.SH "PUBLIC PROPERTIES"
.IX Header "PUBLIC PROPERTIES"
.SS "name"
.IX Subsection "name"
Returns the name of the column.
.SS "type"
.IX Subsection "type"
Returns the data type of the column \- varchar, int, etc.
.SS "length"
.IX Subsection "length"
Returns the size of the field.
.SS "is_nullable"
.IX Subsection "is_nullable"
True or false.
.SS "default_value"
.IX Subsection "default_value"
Returns the default value of the field, if any.
.SS "is_pk"
.IX Subsection "is_pk"
Returns true if the field is a primary key field.  False otherwise.
.SS "key"
.IX Subsection "key"
Returns either \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`primary_key\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`unique\*(C'\fR.
.SS "enum_values"
.IX Subsection "enum_values"
\&\s-1ONLY\s0 if the column is an \f(CW\*(C`enum\*(C'\fR data type, this property will return an arraref 
of the possible enum values.
